cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper deals with using information from real estate market websites to predict the price polarity of properties. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper uses machine learning models based on doc2vec to identify latent semantic content in text descriptions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories as the paper uses machine learning models to learn the correlation between price and information of real estate properties. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of image data, but it is still possible that image data was used in the data set.
